\section{Discussion}

\subsection{In sum}

\miniframeson
\begin{frame}%{Payoffs}
    \begin{itemize}
    \item This is a work in progress.\pause  
    \item In this paper identified {\bf two main gaps} in the literature. We don't know,
      \begin{enumerate}
        \item {\color{blue}The rationale of clientelist targeting}.
        \item {\color{blue}The role of electoral contestation}.\pause
      \end{enumerate}
    \item We {\bf attribute this confusion} to the the fact that the literature takes the {\bf EUT as a starting point}.\pause
    \item We introduced {\bf Prospect Theory} in the vote-buying literature as an {\bf alternative way to understand decision-making under risk}.\pause
    \item To test this theory, we {\bf formalized a theory of vote-buying} and test it in the {\bf lab}.\pause
    \item Results widely conform with Prospect Theory.
  \end{itemize}
\end{frame}%{Payoffs}


